In this article, President Biden responds to various questions from reporters. He states that the US does not support Taiwan's independence and expresses the need for major changes at the southern border. He mentions ongoing negotiations and his willingness to make significant alterations at the border. The President also discusses the support for Ukraine and the political change in Poland, expressing positivity towards the pro-European Union government. When asked about Iran, he mentions delivering messages privately and being confident in preparedness. Lastly, he emphasizes the importance of Republicans passing funding for the border and expresses his intention to take action if necessary.